<refentry lang="en">
<refentryinfo>
    <title>LSINITRD(1)</title>
</refentryinfo>
<refmeta>
<refentrytitle>lsinitrd</refentrytitle>
<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
<refmiscinfo class="source">dracut</refmiscinfo>
<refmiscinfo class="manual">dracut</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>
<refnamediv>
    <refname>lsinitrd</refname>
    <refpurpose>tool to show the contents of an initramfs image</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv id="_synopsis">
<simpara><emphasis role="strong">lsinitrd</emphasis> [<emphasis>OPTION&#8230;</emphasis>] [&lt;image&gt; [&lt;filename&gt; [&lt;filename&gt; [&#8230;] ]]]</simpara>
<simpara><emphasis role="strong">lsinitrd</emphasis> [<emphasis>OPTION&#8230;</emphasis>] -k &lt;kernel-version&gt;</simpara>
</refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1 id="_description">
<title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<simpara>lsinitrd shows the contents of an initramfs image. if &lt;image&gt; is omitted, then
lsinitrd uses the default image <emphasis>/boot/&lt;machine-id&gt;/&lt;kernel-version&gt;/initrd</emphasis> or
<emphasis>/boot/initramfs-&lt;kernel-version&gt;.img</emphasis>.</simpara>
</refsect1>
<refsect1 id="_options">
<title>OPTIONS</title>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<emphasis role="strong">-h, --help</emphasis>
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
    print a help message and exit.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<emphasis role="strong">-s, --size</emphasis>
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
    sort the contents of the initramfs by size.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<emphasis role="strong">-f, --file</emphasis> <emphasis>&lt;filename&gt;</emphasis>
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
    print the contents of &lt;filename&gt;.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<emphasis role="strong">-k, --kver</emphasis> <emphasis>&lt;kernel version&gt;</emphasis>
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
    inspect the initramfs of &lt;kernel version&gt;.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</refsect1>
<refsect1 id="_availability">
<title>AVAILABILITY</title>
<simpara>The lsinitrd command is part of the dracut package and is available from
<ulink url="https://dracut.wiki.kernel.org">https://dracut.wiki.kernel.org</ulink></simpara>
